Jeez.

781
00:51:09,248 --> 00:51:11,307
Get up. Woman.

782
00:51:14,487 --> 00:51:18,082
Oh. No. No. No.

783
00:51:18,157 --> 00:51:20,148
Don't you dare do that.

784
00:51:20,226 --> 00:51:23,024
Get up. Woman.

785
00:51:23,096 --> 00:51:25,826
Goddamn. Evelyn. Get up!

786
00:51:29,936 --> 00:51:31,836
Get up.

787
00:51:38,511 --> 00:51:43,847
Get up. Evelyn. Get up. Get up.

788
00:52:48,453 --> 00:52:50,580
Well. We were wondering
what happened to you.

789
00:52:50,655 --> 00:52:53,180
I thought you'd give public
transportation a break...

790
00:52:53,258 --> 00:52:54,885
come out with your family today.

791
00:52:54,960 --> 00:52:57,554
I always take the train.

792
00:52:57,629 --> 00:53:00,496
I know you like the train. Dad.
Somebody would've picked you up.

793
00:53:00,565 --> 00:53:03,125
Or I would've come
and picked you up.

794
00:53:03,201 --> 00:53:05,431
Where's Uncle Stephen?

795
00:53:05,504 --> 00:53:07,699
He's in bad shape.

796
00:53:07,772 --> 00:53:10,240
The doctor
wouldn't let him come.

797
00:53:10,308 --> 00:53:16,975
Hey. What are all these cars
doing on my place?

798
00:53:17,048 --> 00:53:21,951
They're friends of mom's.
Come to pay their last respects.

799
00:53:26,458 --> 00:53:28,255
When I think of my mother...

800
00:53:31,763 --> 00:53:33,890
I think of her posture...

801
00:53:33,965 --> 00:53:36,832
the way that she carried
herself through life.

802
00:53:36,902 --> 00:53:39,496
She was upright...

803
00:53:39,571 --> 00:53:42,199
with dignity. Always.

804
00:53:44,209 --> 00:53:46,109
And those laser eyes
of hers...

805
00:53:46,178 --> 00:53:49,079
seeing right through you.

806
00:53:49,147 --> 00:53:51,581
One look from her...

807
00:53:51,650 --> 00:53:54,551
and she knew what the truth was.
Whatever the situation was.

808
00:53:58,023 --> 00:54:00,992
When I think of my mother...

809
00:54:01,059 --> 00:54:03,550
I think of the word "grace."

810
00:54:03,628 --> 00:54:08,930
That was a word
that was invented for her.

811
00:54:10,535 --> 00:54:13,732
She set the standard...

812
00:54:13,805 --> 00:54:15,830
in loyalty...

813
00:54:15,907 --> 00:54:17,966
family pride...

814
00:54:18,043 --> 00:54:19,533
and love.

815
00:54:21,112 --> 00:54:23,171
And she taught me well...

816
00:54:25,584 --> 00:54:29,315
in what to look for
when choosing a wife.

817
00:54:31,389 --> 00:54:34,449
So. Mom. I thank you.

818
00:55:11,096 --> 00:55:15,465
Hey. What the hell
are you doing?

819
00:55:15,533 --> 00:55:16,864
I got to pick up
some stuff in town.

820
00:55:16,935 --> 00:55:18,300
I thought I'd take it
for a ride.

821
00:55:18,370 --> 00:55:20,565
What's the matter
with your kraut car?

822
00:55:20,639 --> 00:55:24,735
- It's Japanese. Dad.
- Still the enemy.

823
00:55:24,809 --> 00:55:27,141
We're not at war anymore.
Remember?

824
00:55:27,212 --> 00:55:29,442
They're not the enemy.
They may be yours.

825
00:55:29,514 --> 00:55:34,417
