because of some Nazi bastards.

826
00:55:34,486 --> 00:55:37,387
I know that. All I want to do
is just take it for a spin.

827
00:55:37,455 --> 00:55:40,390
Nobody else drives
this Chevy but me.

828
00:55:40,458 --> 00:55:42,517
Fine. Fine.

829
00:55:42,594 --> 00:55:44,858
You just keep
your precious car.

830
00:55:44,929 --> 00:55:46,920
You shouldn't be driving
a goddamn shopping cart...

831
00:55:46,998 --> 00:55:49,023
better yet a '55 Chevy.

832
00:55:55,607 --> 00:55:57,006
Are you all right. Mitchell?

833
00:55:57,075 --> 00:56:01,405
No.

834
00:56:04,749 --> 00:56:07,013
Was everything
the way you wanted it?

835
00:56:07,085 --> 00:56:08,882
The service?

836
00:56:08,953 --> 00:56:11,353
Not very religious.

837
00:56:11,423 --> 00:56:13,983
You're standing on one leg.

838
00:56:14,059 --> 00:56:15,788
What?

839
00:56:15,860 --> 00:56:19,728
An old prophet
was once asked...

840
00:56:19,798 --> 00:56:23,256
"Can you tell me
the meaning of religion...

841
00:56:23,335 --> 00:56:26,168
"standing on one leg?"

842
00:56:26,237 --> 00:56:28,762
And what did he say?

843
00:56:28,840 --> 00:56:31,274
Do unto others...

844
00:56:31,343 --> 00:56:35,507
as you would have them do
unto you.

845
00:56:35,580 --> 00:56:37,673
That's my belief.

846
00:56:37,749 --> 00:56:40,377
We must be nice to people.

847
00:56:40,452 --> 00:56:42,113
And are you?

848
00:56:42,187 --> 00:56:44,178
God. No.

849
00:56:45,390 --> 00:56:47,119
Did you get the bread?

850
00:56:47,192 --> 00:56:48,454
Yeah.

851
00:56:50,995 --> 00:56:53,759
Do you believe
in doing unto others...

852
00:56:53,832 --> 00:56:57,029
as you would have them
do unto you?

853
00:56:57,102 --> 00:56:58,865
What?

854
00:56:58,937 --> 00:57:01,633
Your father does.

855
00:57:01,706 --> 00:57:06,075
My father believes you do
to others before they do to you.

856
00:57:06,144 --> 00:57:08,840
Sorry. Dad.
I couldn't resist that.

857
00:57:08,913 --> 00:57:11,677
Isn't it time
you learned how. Alex...

858
00:57:11,750 --> 00:57:15,277
at least occasionally.
To resist?

859
00:57:16,821 --> 00:57:18,220
What do you want to eat.
Mitchell?

860
00:57:18,289 --> 00:57:19,449
Fish.

861
00:57:19,524 --> 00:57:22,015
We have whitefish.
And we have lox.

862
00:57:22,093 --> 00:57:24,527
Fresh fish.

863
00:57:24,596 --> 00:57:26,723
We don't have any fresh.

864
00:57:26,798 --> 00:57:28,231
We have a lake.

865
00:57:29,334 --> 00:57:32,064
Well. Why don't
you and Alex...

866
00:57:32,137 --> 00:57:35,265
take the boat out
and go catch a fish?

867
00:57:35,340 --> 00:57:37,331
Now?

868
00:57:37,409 --> 00:57:39,138
Rebecca. This is ridiculous.

869
00:57:40,378 --> 00:57:43,939
I need a partner
to row the boat.

870
00:57:44,015 --> 00:57:45,346
You and me both.

871
00:57:47,852 --> 00:57:49,547
Your father needs a partner.

872
00:57:49,621 --> 00:57:51,179
Asher!

873
00:57:51,256 --> 00:57:53,383
Ah. Jesus.

874
00:57:57,562 --> 00:58:00,429
Your father's asking
for your company.

875
00:58:00,498 --> 00:58:02,363
