01:24:54,344 --> 01:24:56,505
Over there! Let's get 'em!

1259
01:24:58,715 --> 01:25:00,876
- Abby Staley!
- With a pet!

1260
01:25:00,950 --> 01:25:03,418
Quick. It's Shea! Let's go!
Out the back gate!

1261
01:25:03,486 --> 01:25:05,317
Where the hell are you going?
Come here!

1262
01:25:05,388 --> 01:25:07,788
Leave me alone!

1263
01:25:07,857 --> 01:25:10,155
What. You don't like me
anymore. Abby?

1264
01:25:10,226 --> 01:25:12,217
- You're a good kid. Aren't you?
- Leave him alone!

1265
01:25:12,295 --> 01:25:14,092
What. He can't speak
for himself?

1266
01:25:14,164 --> 01:25:17,429
Leave him alone.
You shithead.

1267
01:25:17,500 --> 01:25:19,491
You believe the language?

1268
01:25:19,569 --> 01:25:20,729
Sixth grade gutter whore.

1269
01:25:20,804 --> 01:25:23,272
You think I wouldn't find you?

1270
01:25:23,339 --> 01:25:26,331
That's your little game.
Huh. Abby?

1271
01:25:26,409 --> 01:25:29,105
Leave me alone. My brother
will beat the shit out of you.

1272
01:25:30,447 --> 01:25:31,778
That's for your brother.

1273
01:25:31,848 --> 01:25:34,316
- Leave her alone. Shithead!
- Get him!

1274
01:25:36,319 --> 01:25:37,513
You little rat!

1275
01:25:40,590 --> 01:25:43,320
Shit! He broke my Tony Hawk!
Damn it!

1276
01:25:43,393 --> 01:25:46,191
He broke my goddamn board!

1277
01:25:46,262 --> 01:25:49,527
Go get her! Come on!

1278
01:25:49,599 --> 01:25:51,567
Get up!

1279
01:25:51,634 --> 01:25:53,693
- Get 'em!
- Come on!

1280
01:25:53,770 --> 01:25:55,931
Come on! Let's go!

1281
01:25:57,307 --> 01:25:59,605
- Come on!
- You all right. Shea?

1282
01:26:24,200 --> 01:26:28,000
Please be careful.
Can you handle it?

1283
01:26:28,071 --> 01:26:30,039
Yeah. I got it.

1284
01:26:30,106 --> 01:26:31,630
I think so.

1285
01:26:37,814 --> 01:26:40,282
OK. We'll put him in the bow.

1286
01:26:42,919 --> 01:26:45,854
Now. Watch out
for the ledge right there.

1287
01:26:45,922 --> 01:26:48,049
Yeah. Dad. Where's the bow?

1288
01:26:53,429 --> 01:26:54,987
Right in here.

1289
01:26:57,233 --> 01:27:02,034
Shit. My back.
Christ. My back.

1290
01:27:02,105 --> 01:27:04,903
Dad. What are you doing?
You could hurt yourself.

1291
01:27:04,974 --> 01:27:06,942
Someone has to do it.

1292
01:27:13,082 --> 01:27:16,245
Dad. This is absurd.
This is totally absurd.

1293
01:27:16,319 --> 01:27:18,310
It is not.

1294
01:27:18,388 --> 01:27:23,382
He lived by the sea.
Now he dies by the sea.

1295
01:27:23,459 --> 01:27:25,791
This is not a sea. Dad.

1296
01:27:25,862 --> 01:27:28,228
This is Lake Winnipac.
It's not the Atlantic.

1297
01:27:28,298 --> 01:27:32,098
It's a sailor's sky tonight.

1298
01:27:32,168 --> 01:27:35,296
He was in the navy. Dad.
He wasn't a Viking.

1299
01:27:35,371 --> 01:27:38,636
This is what he always wanted.

1300
01:27:38,708 --> 01:27:41,040
This is what he gets.

1301
01:27:41,110 --> 01:27:42,907
Dad. We got
neighbors here. OK?

1302
01:27:42,979 --> 01:27:44,970
The hell with them!

1303
01:27:54,824 --> 01:27:57,224
Jesus.

1304
01:28:03,166 --> 01:28:05,430
Dad?

1305
01:28:05,501 --> 01:28:10,200
I'm fine. I'm fine.

1306
01:28:10,273 --> 01:28:13,106
He held on for a while.
Didn't he?

1307
01:28:13,176 --> 01:28:16,634
The only way he knew how.

1308
01:28:16,713 --> 01:28:20,410
You could have learned
a thing or two from him.

1309
01:28:20,483 --> 01:28:21,973
No. I did.

1310
01:28:22,051 --> 01:28:26,078
I learned how to tie
36 different ship knots.

1311
01:28:26,155 --> 01:28:28,419
The hell with knots.

1312
01:28:28,491 --> 01:28:30,857
The man had character.

1313
01:28:30,927 --> 01:28:33,487
You could have learned
that from him.

1314
01:28:33,596 --> 01:28:35,496
I tried to learn that from you.

1315
01:28:44,907 --> 01:28:46,397
I'm getting blisters.

1316
01:28:46,476 --> 01:28:48,410
Let's go over here.

1317
01:29:03,693 --> 01:29:07,151
So. How come you hang out with
that asshole morgan Cooper?

1318
01:29:07,230 --> 01:29:08,288
I don't know.

1319
01:29:08,364 --> 01:29:11,333
How come you ran away
with that guy?

1320
01:29:11,401 --> 01:29:14,029
I don't know.
Thought he was cool. I guess.

1321
01:29:14,103 --> 01:29:15,730
Was he?

1322
01:29:15,805 --> 01:29:17,830
No.

1323
01:29:17,907 --> 01:29:19,772
Where'd you go?

1324
01:29:19,842 --> 01:29:21,673
Cape Cod.

1325
01:29:21,744 --> 01:29:24,235
Why'd you come back?

1326
01:29:24,314 --> 01:29:28,250
I don't know.
Guess I got bored.

1327
01:29:28,318 --> 01:29:30,013
Were you homesick?

1328
01:29:30,086 --> 01:29:31,883
Hell. No.

1329
01:29:35,758 --> 01:29:37,555
I don't know.

1330
01:29:37,627 --> 01:29:40,892
Maybe. A little.

1331
01:29:40,963 --> 01:29:42,794
I get homesick
when I go to camp.

1332
01:29:42,865 --> 01:29:46,858
That's 'cause camp sucks.

1333
01:29:46,936 --> 01:29:48,836
Are your parents
as boring and angry...

1334
01:29:48,905 --> 01:29:51,373
and always screaming
at each other like mine?

1335
01:29:51,441 --> 01:29:52,499
Kind of.

1336
01:29:52,575 --> 01:29:54,805
Do they never
talk to you like mine?

1337
01:29:54,877 --> 01:29:57,778
No. My parents are
always talking to me.

1338
01:29:57,847 --> 01:30:00,407
They ask me questions
whenever they can.

1339
01:30:00,483 --> 01:30:02,212
You're lucky.

1340
01:30:02,285 --> 01:30:05,584
No. I'm not. You're lucky.

1341
01:30:10,259 --> 01:30:12,124
It's OK.

1342
01:30:15,631 --> 01:30:17,963
You really do like it.

1343
01:30:20,803 --> 01:30:22,794
How come you haven't
tried to kiss me?

1344
01:30:22,872 --> 01:30:25,966
What? I don't know.

1345
01:30:27,877 --> 01:30:29,708
Do you want to?

1346
01:30:29,779 --> 01:30:32,339
I don't know.

1347
01:30:32,415 --> 01:30:36,579
'Cause. Like. You can.
You know. If you want to.

1348
01:30:36,652 --> 01:30:40,213
No. Thank you.

1349
01:30:42,325 --> 01:30:44,850
OK.

1350
01:31:08,418 --> 01:31:10,716
Go. Asher.

1351
01:31:10,787 --> 01:31:12,880
Break it down. Asher.

1352
01:31:14,357 --> 01:31:15,790
Go. Asher. Go. Asher.

1353
01:31:18,261 --> 01:31:19,353
Police!

1354
01:31:19,429 --> 01:31:23,092
What's going on here?
What's all this noise?

1355
01:31:27,703 --> 01:31:29,637
Asher! Asher!

1356
01:31:29,705 --> 01:31:31,468
Where the hell do you think
you're going?

1357
01:31:31,541 --> 01:31:32,838
What are you doing?

1358
01:31:32,909 --> 01:31:33,967
Against the wall.

1359
01:31:34,043 --> 01:31:36,944
Spread your legs.
Spread your legs.

1360
01:31:37,013 --> 01:31:37,980
Asher!

1361
01:31:38,047 --> 01:31:39,605
I'm so sorry. Peg.

1362
01:31:39,682 --> 01:31:43,846
I'll give you something
to be sorry about.

1363
01:31:43,920 --> 01:31:45,478
My keys. My keys.

1364
01:31:48,658 --> 01:31:51,092
Asher.

1365
01:31:51,160 --> 01:31:52,991
What have you gotten into?

1366
01:31:54,230 --> 01:31:55,288
What's happening?

1367
01:31:55,364 --> 01:31:56,888
Hey. No talking.

1368
01:31:56,966 --> 01:31:58,365
Jesus.

1369
01:31:59,469 --> 01:32:00,902
Jesus. Man.
What are you doing?

1370
01:32:00,970 --> 01:32:04,599
I can't believe I trusted you.

1371
01:32:04,674 --> 01:32:05,868
Closet back here?

1372
01:32:05,942 --> 01:32:08,604
No. I don't know.
It's not mine.

1373
01:32:08,678 --> 01:32:09,645
Yeah. Right.

1374
01:32:09,712 --> 01:32:11,873
Let's get this
out of the way.

1375
01:32:11,948 --> 01:32:13,677
Move that thing.

1376
01:32:16,285 --> 01:32:17,217
You got a key for this?

1377
01:32:17,286 --> 01:32:19,254
No. I told you.
I've never used it before.

1378
01:32:19,322 --> 01:32:21,119
Come on. Get something...
anything.

1379
01:32:21,190 --> 01:32:22,851
Give me the door lock.

1380
01:32:22,925 --> 01:32:24,119
Asher.

1381
01:32:31,400 --> 01:32:32,367
Oh. My God.

1382
01:32:33,769 --> 01:32:35,100
Holy shit.

1383
01:32:35,171 --> 01:32:36,570
Jackpot.

1384
01:32:36,639 --> 01:32:39,130
How about this
for a noise complaint?

1385
01:32:39,208 --> 01:32:41,039
Wow. We're looking
at fiFTeen years here.

1386
01:32:41,110 --> 01:32:43,840
What do you think? There must
be eight plants in here.

1387
01:32:43,913 --> 01:32:45,847
I don't want anything
to do with you ever again.

1388
01:32:45,915 --> 01:32:48,907
Peg. I'm so sorry. I didn't mean
to get you in trouble.

1389
01:32:48,985 --> 01:32:50,418
I'll do something. I promise.

1390
01:32:50,486 --> 01:32:52,351
I can see the headlines now...

1391
01:32:52,421 --> 01:32:56,356
"Father and son burn uncle
in makeshiFT Viking funeral.

1392
01:32:56,425 --> 01:33:00,122
"Wife and children shamed."

1393
01:33:00,196 --> 01:33:02,426
Is this legal. Dad?

1394
01:33:05,201 --> 01:33:06,896
All right. So what do we do?

1395
01:33:06,969 --> 01:33:09,802
We say something or...

1396
01:33:09,872 --> 01:33:11,669
It's not about words.

1397
01:33:11,741 --> 01:33:13,709
I'm sorry. Of course.
You've done this before.

1398
01:33:13,776 --> 01:33:18,145
It's about this man's
connection with the sea.

1399
01:33:18,214 --> 01:33:21,479
It's not about you or me...

1400
01:33:21,551 --> 01:33:24,384
or words of grace.

1401
01:33:24,453 --> 01:33:26,785
Push it to the water line.

1402
01:33:26,856 --> 01:33:27,982
All right.

1403
01:33:35,498 --> 01:33:36,965
Now...

1404
01:33:38,267 --> 01:33:40,929
when I say. "Ahoy"...

1405
01:33:41,003 --> 01:33:43,597
give it a big shove
out to sea.

1406
01:33:43,673 --> 01:33:46,164
Aye. Aye. Captain.

1407
01:33:46,242 --> 01:33:48,267
Sorry. Dad.

1408
01:33:50,513 --> 01:33:52,708
Look. We don't have to do this.
You know that.

1409
01:33:52,782 --> 01:33:54,909
We're doing it.

1410
01:33:56,886 --> 01:33:58,911
Ahoy. Ahoy!

1411
01:34:46,736 --> 01:34:48,601
We got to go. Dad.

1412
01:34:48,671 --> 01:34:50,263
Dad. Dad. Come on.
We got to go.

1413
01:34:50,339 --> 01:34:53,399
Dad. We got to go.

1414
01:35:00,583 --> 01:35:02,448
Thank you. Alex.

1415
01:35:04,920 --> 01:35:06,478
Thank you.

1416
01:35:20,202 --> 01:35:21,863
You know. We could go to jail.

1417
01:35:21,937 --> 01:35:25,896
If we're lucky.
We might be cellmates.

1418
01:35:28,844 --> 01:35:30,937
Yeah. Hi. Honey.

1419
01:35:33,282 --> 01:35:34,715
What?

1420
01:35:36,786 --> 01:35:39,448
Bec. Is he OK?
Where is he?

1421
01:35:39,522 --> 01:35:42,616
They're processing his papers.
They had to fingerprint him.

1422
01:35:42,692 --> 01:35:43,716
Oh. Jesus.

1423
01:35:43,793 --> 01:35:45,454
He'll probably get off.
The little sneak.

1424
01:35:45,528 --> 01:35:47,086
The police
didn't have a warrant.

1425
01:35:47,163 --> 01:35:49,256
- Thank God.
- He's always getting off.

1426
01:35:49,331 --> 01:35:51,390
That's part
of the problem. Alex.

1427
01:35:51,467 --> 01:35:54,027
It can't go on like this
any longer.

1428
01:35:56,372 --> 01:35:59,034
Look at us.
Can you believe this?

1429
01:35:59,108 --> 01:36:01,235
You OK?

1430
01:36:01,310 --> 01:36:03,904
I'm still here. Aren't I?

1431
01:36:16,092 --> 01:36:18,026
Asher. Honey.

1432
01:36:18,094 --> 01:36:20,153
I didn't know the shit
was there. Mom. I swear.

1433
01:36:20,229 --> 01:36:23,426
Save it. Asher. Do you realize
how serious this is?

1434
01:36:27,503 --> 01:36:29,061
I'm so sorry. Dad.

1435
01:36:29,138 --> 01:36:31,538
I'm sorry. Too. Buddy.

1436
01:36:31,607 --> 01:36:33,040
I'm sorry. Too.

1437
01:36:33,109 --> 01:36:34,098
Oh. God.

1438
01:36:34,176 --> 01:36:35,666
Asher. Do you know
you could've gotten...

1439
01:36:35,745 --> 01:36:38,077
up to fiFTeen years for this?

1440
01:36:38,147 --> 01:36:39,341
I'm such a screw-up.

1441
01:36:39,415 --> 01:36:41,042
You're not.
You are not a screw-up.

1442
01:36:41,117 --> 01:36:43,142
- Yes. I am.
- You're not.

1443
01:36:43,219 --> 01:36:44,584
Does Pappy have
to see me this way?

1444
01:36:44,653 --> 01:36:48,089
Everything's screwed up. Dad.

1445
01:36:48,157 --> 01:36:49,419
Everything's shit. Dad.

1446
01:36:49,492 --> 01:36:52,325
I was with this girl
who was there.

1447
01:36:52,394 --> 01:36:54,259
She didn't do anything.

1448
01:36:54,330 --> 01:36:56,696
I don't know where she is.
She's going to hate me now.

1449
01:36:56,766 --> 01:36:58,631
This just gets
better and better.

1450
01:36:58,701 --> 01:36:59,929
It's OK. It's OK.

1451
01:37:00,002 --> 01:37:01,799
You have to help her.
Please. Dad.

1452
01:37:01,871 --> 01:37:03,304
We got to make sure
she's all right.

1453
01:37:03,372 --> 01:37:05,272
It's all right. Asher.
We'll take care of her.

1454
01:37:05,341 --> 01:37:07,935
Don't worry about her.
She'll be all right.

1455
01:37:08,010 --> 01:37:09,807
There was no search warrant.
Thank God.

1456
01:37:09,879 --> 01:37:10,868
It's OK.

1457
01:37:10,946 --> 01:37:14,347
And I've also screwed up
with school. Mom.

1458
01:37:14,416 --> 01:37:15,974
I'm going to have to go
back for another year.

1459
01:37:16,051 --> 01:37:17,985
You're failing
your senior year?

1460
01:37:18,053 --> 01:37:19,315
My life is shit!

1461
01:37:19,388 --> 01:37:20,787
You're a bright kid.
For God's sake.

1462
01:37:20,856 --> 01:37:22,983
I just couldn't do it.
I couldn't get into it.

1463
01:37:23,058 --> 01:37:25,083
What the hell can you do?
Sell drugs?

1464
01:37:25,161 --> 01:37:27,026
Now. Wait a minute.
Let's face this. All right?

1465
01:37:27,096 --> 01:37:29,462
We have all been in our own
little worlds. Haven't we?

1466
01:37:29,532 --> 01:37:31,796
It's going to stop right now.

1467
01:37:31,867 --> 01:37:35,303
We're a family. We're going
to figure this out together.

1468
01:37:35,371 --> 01:37:37,430
Figure what out?
This? And school and...

1469
01:37:37,506 --> 01:37:40,031
And everything else.
That's right.

1470
01:37:41,677 --> 01:37:45,841
Asher. You're not
a kid anymore.

1471
01:37:45,915 --> 01:37:49,612
You got to find out what
is important in your life...

1472
01:37:49,685 --> 01:37:54,713
what do you love. And you let
nothing get in the way of it.

1473
01:37:56,458 --> 01:38:01,452
Asher. Listen to your father.

1474
01:38:01,530 --> 01:38:04,465
He knows what
he's talking about.

1475
01:38:06,468 --> 01:38:08,493
Oh. God.

1476
01:38:08,571 --> 01:38:09,833
Who's calling you now?

1477
01:38:09,905 --> 01:38:12,499
I don't know.
This is probably a patient.

1478
01:38:12,575 --> 01:38:13,507
Hello.

1479
01:38:13,576 --> 01:38:15,510
- Mrs. Gromberg?
- Yes.

1480
01:38:15,578 --> 01:38:17,944
This is mrs. Hodgson.
Is Eli with you?

1481
01:38:18,013 --> 01:38:19,002
What?

1482
01:38:19,081 --> 01:38:20,480
He disappeared
from the dance tonight...

1483
01:38:29,491 --> 01:38:31,686
Is he in there?

1484
01:38:31,760 --> 01:38:33,057
Yeah.

1485
01:38:41,937 --> 01:38:44,371
You are staying here
with us tonight.

1486
01:38:44,440 --> 01:38:47,034
I don't want you
out of my sight.

1487
01:38:47,109 --> 01:38:48,269
Where should I sleep?

1488
01:38:48,344 --> 01:38:51,802
Why don't you sleep
in your old room with Eli?

1489
01:38:51,881 --> 01:38:54,179
We've got a lot
of talking to do.

1490
01:38:54,250 --> 01:38:55,342
But in the morning.

1491
01:38:55,417 --> 01:38:58,079
I couldn't take one more
surprise tonight.

1492
01:38:58,153 --> 01:38:59,245
Good night. Honey.

1493
01:38:59,321 --> 01:39:01,118
I'm going to bed.

1494
01:39:01,190 --> 01:39:03,317
- Good night. Mom.
- Good night. Boys.

1495
01:39:03,392 --> 01:39:04,882
What about me?

1496
01:39:06,495 --> 01:39:07,962
What about you?

1497
01:39:08,030 --> 01:39:09,895
Where do I sleep?

1498
01:39:12,601 --> 01:39:13,898
Couch.

1499
01:39:28,851 --> 01:39:30,614
What are you doing?

1500
01:39:30,686 --> 01:39:32,620
I was getting
in bed with my wife.

1501
01:39:32,688 --> 01:39:37,318
Are you out of your mind?
Aren't things confusing enough?

1502
01:39:37,393 --> 01:39:39,884
We have two kids.
Both of them weird.

1503
01:39:39,962 --> 01:39:41,327
Very weird. Alex.

1504
01:39:41,397 --> 01:39:43,695
One of them is a drug dealer.
And the other one is...

1505
01:39:43,766 --> 01:39:45,927
What's Eli? He's what?

1506
01:39:46,001 --> 01:39:47,628
I don't know
what the other one is.

1507
01:39:47,703 --> 01:39:51,639
But. Alex. Do you want
to work at this?

1508
01:39:51,707 --> 01:39:53,766
- Yes.
- Really work at this?

1509
01:39:53,842 --> 01:39:55,104
Yes. I do. Yes.

1510
01:39:55,177 --> 01:39:56,610
Will you see her again?

1511
01:39:56,679 --> 01:40:01,912
No. I'm not...
I wasn't seeing her.

1512
01:40:01,984 --> 01:40:05,181
Look. Rebecca.
I got sidetracked...

1513
01:40:05,254 --> 01:40:09,520
with the office
and the soup kitchen...

1514
01:40:09,591 --> 01:40:12,389
and I wasn't paying attention.

1515
01:40:17,700 --> 01:40:21,693
Life... it's always getting
in the way of us. Isn't it?

1516
01:40:23,272 --> 01:40:24,239
Yeah.

1517
01:40:26,875 --> 01:40:29,002
- The couch.
- Rebecca.

1518
01:40:29,078 --> 01:40:30,739
The couch.

1519
01:40:36,852 --> 01:40:38,911
- Alex?
- Yeah.

1520
01:40:40,456 --> 01:40:43,357
In the morning. There are
three things you can do.

1521
01:40:43,425 --> 01:40:45,620
You can get our son
a good lawyer...

1522
01:40:45,694 --> 01:40:49,357
find us a marriage counselor...

1523
01:40:49,431 --> 01:40:51,865
and you can wash the dishes...

1524
01:40:53,202 --> 01:40:55,568
in our kitchen.

1525
01:40:58,540 --> 01:41:01,373
I love you. Bec.
Good night.

1526
01:41:04,179 --> 01:41:06,875
I love you. Too.

1527
01:41:13,856 --> 01:41:16,120
What the hell
are you doing. Dad?

1528
01:41:16,191 --> 01:41:18,159
Insulin.

1529
01:41:18,227 --> 01:41:20,889
Your mother used to do this.

1530
01:41:27,202 --> 01:41:28,999
You going to be
comfortable here?

1531
01:41:29,071 --> 01:41:34,236
In the war. I slept
in blood-filled trenches.

1532
01:41:34,309 --> 01:41:35,901
Hope you don't mind
if I join you.

1533
01:41:35,978 --> 01:41:38,879
No. You take this couch.

1534
01:41:40,616 --> 01:41:42,208
Thanks. Dad.

1535
01:41:44,353 --> 01:41:46,913
Still in the doghouse?

1536
01:41:51,860 --> 01:41:54,658
Well. Dad. I thought
we'd relive my childhood.

1537
01:41:54,730 --> 01:41:57,130
You know. All those nights
we went out camping together.

1538
01:41:57,199 --> 01:41:58,666
Yeah. I remember.

1539
01:41:58,734 --> 01:42:02,170
- Oh. Yeah. In your dreams.
- You were a pain in the ass.

1540
01:42:02,237 --> 01:42:06,833
Yeah. We had a lot of nights
out together. Didn't we. Dad?

1541
01:42:06,909 --> 01:42:09,707
You should've seen him.
He was. Like. Seven feet tall.

1542
01:42:09,778 --> 01:42:12,975
Huge. Like The Rock.
When he swung his board at me...

1543
01:42:13,048 --> 01:42:15,107
I just put my fist
right through it.

1544
01:42:15,184 --> 01:42:17,345
Broke it in half...
A Tony Hawk. Too.

1545
01:42:17,419 --> 01:42:19,250
And when he got up.
He charged at me.

1546
01:42:19,321 --> 01:42:21,812
But I just went like this.
And I kicked him in the shin.

1547
01:42:21,890 --> 01:42:24,188
Then I went...

1548
01:42:24,259 --> 01:42:27,228
right in his mug.
Laid him out.

1549
01:42:27,296 --> 01:42:30,094
Smack in the kisser.

1550
01:42:30,165 --> 01:42:31,655
Good night. Boys!

1551
01:42:31,733 --> 01:42:32,961
Good night. Eli!

1552
01:42:33,035 --> 01:42:34,832
Good night. Pappy.
Good night. Dad.

1553
01:42:34,903 --> 01:42:36,131
Night. Dad. Night. Pappy.

1554
01:42:36,205 --> 01:42:37,763
Good night. Mom.

1555
01:42:37,840 --> 01:42:38,864
Night. Mom.

1556
01:42:38,941 --> 01:42:44,401
Good night.

1557
01:42:46,014 --> 01:42:48,983
You'll never know

1558
01:42:49,051 --> 01:42:51,679
How much I love you

1559
01:43:00,829 --> 01:43:04,094
How many verses
do you know. Dad?

1560
01:43:04,166 --> 01:43:08,432
It's a lullaby
that puts me to sleep.

1561
01:43:12,875 --> 01:43:14,843
It's keeping me awake.

1562
01:43:19,615 --> 01:43:21,480
Bro.

1563
01:43:21,550 --> 01:43:24,018
What's that bracelet all about?

1564
01:43:24,086 --> 01:43:26,577
You get that for taking care
of your lady?

1565
01:43:26,655 --> 01:43:31,456
No. Man. That's
a good thing. Buddy.

1566
01:43:31,527 --> 01:43:33,461
I wish I had done the same.

1567
01:43:37,733 --> 01:43:41,794
I'll never find

1568
01:43:41,870 --> 01:43:43,098
I never could hide

1569
01:43:43,172 --> 01:43:49,338
I guess I'm not the father
I thought I was.

1570
01:43:49,411 --> 01:43:53,541
I got one kid
who could be in the can.

1571
01:43:53,615 --> 01:43:56,015
And the other one...

1572
01:43:56,084 --> 01:43:58,416
There's something about him.
I don't know what it is.

1573
01:43:58,487 --> 01:44:03,186
You know. When we were kids.
Stephen and I...

1574
01:44:03,258 --> 01:44:05,317
we got in trouble
with the cops.

1575
01:44:05,394 --> 01:44:08,386
Really? You never told me.
What for?

1576
01:44:08,463 --> 01:44:11,830
Selling booze
that fell off a truck.

1577
01:44:11,900 --> 01:44:14,198
We did OK. Too.

1578
01:44:21,243 --> 01:44:23,939
Dad. I'm thinking about
leaving the firm.

1579
01:44:25,480 --> 01:44:30,110
I want to try
public office again.

1580
01:44:30,185 --> 01:44:35,714
I've waited ten years
to hear you say that.

1581
01:44:35,791 --> 01:44:37,952
Really?

1582
01:44:38,026 --> 01:44:40,893
Maybe this time
you'll vote for me?

1583
01:44:45,267 --> 01:44:47,929
Not a chance in hell.

1584
01:45:06,021 --> 01:45:07,989
Dad. You're not planning
on this becoming...

1585
01:45:08,056 --> 01:45:10,286
